(2593, 1, '2018-04-10 17:27:47', '2018-04-10 17:27:47', 'I was forever making excuses – telling myself I’d join a gym next month, or once I got a big project out of the way. But it never happened. Until, finally, last summer I seamlessly settled into a regular fitness routine.\r\n\r\nAt first I worried it was just a phase, but 12 months have passed and I’m still working out four to five times a week. It has been a <em>huge</em> lifestyle change, and here are the simple tactics that made it possible…\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n[gallery size="large" link="file" ids="2158,2160,2159"]\r\n<h5>Where Would We Wear Knit Denim?</h5>\r\nAnywhere! That is the beauty of this fabric. You can be looking your best in your denim blues, but feeling as though you’re wearing track pants!\r\n<blockquote>These Elora Super Skinny Jeans are my new go-to when I’m travelling. They’re a really bright\r\n<cite>Katy Malkovich</cite></blockquote>\r\n<h5>Any Special Care Tips?</h5>\r\nCaring for knit denim is easy, you can just treat your knit jeans the same way you care for regular denim. Turn them inside out and wash them in cold water with mild detergent. Then simply dry them inside out on the line in the shade, or on cool tumble dry.\r\n\r\nCan we look forward to seeing more knit denim styles coming in?\r\nWe will continue to have knit styles through Winter and into Summer too, in new lighter weights.', 'Rich Content Post', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'rich-content-post', '', '', '2018-04-10 17:28:49', '2018-04-10 17:28:49', '', 0, 'http://ellie.themes.zone/?p=2593', 0, 'post', '', 0),
